# Context Model Rule

When the user asks to draw or review a context model, define the system boundary first.

Use exactly one `System`. Model people, organizations, devices, services, and third-party dependencies outside the boundary as `Actor` or `ExternalSystem`.

Do not connect Actor or ExternalSystem directly to System to express interaction. Use interfaces:

- System provides an interface; Actor or ExternalSystem uses or depends on it.
- Actor or ExternalSystem provides an interface; System uses or depends on it.

Output:

- Context diagram code or modeling instructions.
- External participant table.
- Interface table with provider, consumer, purpose, and assumptions.
- Boundary decisions and open questions.

Validate:

- Exactly one System.
- Every external interaction crosses an Interface.
- External participants are not modeled as internal logical components.
